<placeName cert="high" full="yes">Oxyrhynchus</placeName></head><div lang="grc" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete" type="edition"><div n="r" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete" type="textpart"><ab part="N">

    <lb n="1"/><choice><corr>Πόπλιος</corr><sic>ποπλις</sic></choice> Ἀπολλωνίῳ τῶι 

    <lb n="2"/>ἀδελφῶι χαίρειν. 

    <lb n="3"/><choice><corr>γίγνωσκειν</corr><sic>γεινωσκειν</sic></choice> σε θέλω ὅτι <choice><corr>παρα-

    <lb n="4"/>γενόμενος</corr><sic>παραγεναμενος</sic></choice> ἐν τῇ Δίωνος ἐ-

    <lb n="5"/>ζήτησα τοὺς περὶ Μακρεῖνον 

    <lb n="6"/>καὶ οὐχ εὗρον αὐτούς. ὕστερον <choice><corr>γε-

    <lb n="7"/>νόμενος</corr><sic>γεναμενος</sic></choice> ἐν τῇ Χαιρήου εὗρον 

    <lb n="8"/>τὸν Μακρεῖνον νοσοῦντα καὶ 

    <lb n="9"/>ἐτάξατο ὅτι ἐὰν ἀναλάβω ἐμαυ-

    <lb n="10"/>τὸν εὐθέως ἐλεύσομαί σοι εἰς 

    <lb n="11"/>Ἀλεξάνδρειαν μετὰ τῶν ἀν-

    <lb n="12"/>θρώπων τῶν ἀπὸ Πακέρκη. 

    <lb n="13"/>ἔφην δὲ αὐτῷ ὅτι ἐάν μοι <choice><corr>παρα-

    <lb n="14"/>δῷς</corr><sic>παραδοις</sic></choice> μοι τοὺς ἀνθρώπους φιλαν-

    <lb n="15"/>θρωπηθήσῃ· καλῶς οὖν ποι-

    <lb n="16"/>ήσεις, ἄδ<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">ελ</supplied><unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">φ</unclear>ε, τὰ περὶ τὴν 

    <lb n="17"/>ἐπίκρισιν ἀπάρτισον. μὴ ἐπι-

    <lb n="18"/>λάθῃ τὸ μέρος τοῦ ἐργαστηρίου. 

    <lb n="19"/>καὶ Ἐπίμαχος <choice><corr>ἀπογραψάσθω</corr><sic>απογραψαστω</sic></choice> 

    <lb n="20"/>τὸ μέρος τοῦ καμηλῶνος 

    <lb n="21"/>ὃν κατέλειψε αὐτῷ ὁ πατὴρ 

    <lb n="22"/>αὐτοῦ Πλουτίων. ἄσπασαι Ὡρίω-

    <lb n="23"/>να καὶ Τασσευοῦν καὶ Ἀμμώνιον 

    <lb n="24"/>καὶ Ἑλένην <add place="supralinear">καὶ Ἀπολλώνιον</add> καὶ τὰ ἀβάσκαντά 

    <lb n="25"/>σου παιδία. ἀσπάζεταί σε Ἰσίδω-

    <lb n="26"/>ρος καὶ Ὡρίωνα καὶ Ἀμμώνιον 

    <lb n="27"/>καὶ Διογένην. καὶ <choice><corr>μέλει</corr><sic>μελι</sic></choice> μοι περὶ 

    <lb n="28"/>τῶν ἀνθρώπων καὶ συνέβαλον 

    <lb n="29"/>αὐτοῖς σὺν τῷ πατρί μου Ποπλίῳ. 

    <lb n="30"/>ἄ<supplied cert="high" reason="lost">σ</supplied><unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">π</unclear>ασαι τὰ ἀβάσκαντά σου παιδία. 

    <lb n="31"/>ἐρρῶσθαί σε <expan>εὔχ<ex cert="high">ομαι</ex></expan> 

    <lb n="32"/>Φαῶφι <num value="30">λ</num> 
</ab></div><div n="v" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete" type="textpart"><ab part="N">

    <lb n="33"/>Ἀπολλωνίωι <g type="x"/> <expan><unclear cert="high" reason="undefined">π</unclear><ex cert="high">αρὰ</ex></expan> Ποπλίου <abbr>ξυλεμ</abbr> </ab></div></div><div n="meta.26861" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete" type="description"><p><rs cert="high" type="material">Papyrus</rs></p></div><div n="meta.26861" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete" subtype="textDate" type="commentary"><p><date notAfter="200" notBefore="101" type="textDate">II</date></p></div><div n="meta.26861" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete" subtype="general" type="commentary"><p>Tag: 27. (28.) Okt.</p></div><div n="meta.26861" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete" subtype="principalEdition" type="bibliography"><listBibl default="NO"><bibl default="NO" subtype="principal" type="publication"><title level="s" type="abbreviated">P.Oxy.</title><biblScope type="volume">41</biblScope><biblScope type="numbers">2981</biblScope></bibl><bibl default="NO" type="Trismegistos"><biblScope type="numbers">26861</biblScope></bibl><bibl default="NO" type="DDbDP"><series>0181</series>; <biblScope type="volume">41</biblScope>; <biblScope type="numbers">2981</biblScope></bibl></listBibl><p>Perseus links: <xref evaluate="all" from="ROOT" href="0181;41;2981" targOrder="Y" to="DITTO" type="Perseus">Text in Perseus</xref></p></div><div n="meta.26861" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete" subtype="corrections" type="bibliography"><head>BL-Einträge nach BL-Konkordanz</head><listBibl default="NO"><bibl default="NO" type="BL"><biblScope type="volume">VIII</biblScope>, S. <biblScope type="pages">264</biblScope></bibl><bibl default="NO" type="BL"><biblScope type="volume">XI</biblScope>, S. <biblScope type="pages">166</biblScope></bibl></listBibl></div><div n="meta.26861" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete" subtype="illustrations" type="bibliography"><p>keine</p></div><div n="meta.26861" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete" subtype="locations" type="history"><p><placeName cert="high"